 {"id":"frankenjax-hdk","title":"Implement complex unary ops in eval_unary_elementwise (fj-lax arithmetic.rs)","description":"CONTEXT: eval_unary_elementwise() at fj-lax/src/arithmetic.rs has TWO stubs (scalar at ~line 1038, tensor at ~line 1075) returning complex arithmetic not yet implemented when a unary op receives Complex64/Complex128 input.\n\nSCOPE: For ops that JAX supports on complex (sign, square, reciprocal, is_finite): implement the complex logic. For ops JAX does NOT support on complex (floor, ceil, round, lgamma, digamma, erf, erfc, erf_inv): change error to not supported for complex dtype (permanent correct error, not deferred).\n\nCHANGES: 1) Scalar match (line ~1038): dispatch Complex64/Complex128 to per-op complex implementations. 2) Tensor match (line ~1075): same dispatch for tensor elements. 3) Ops unsupported on complex get descriptive permanent error.\n\nTESTING: sign(1+1i)=(1+1i)/sqrt(2), reciprocal(2+0i)=0.5+0i, is_finite(1+2i)=true, floor(complex) returns not supported error. Verify all existing tests pass; log before/after test counts.\n\nACCEPTANCE: Lines ~1038 and ~1075 no longer contain not yet implemented.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-03T00:22:05.837354341Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-03T02:07:33.850145069Z","closed_at":"2026-04-03T02:07:33.849895026Z","close_reason":"Completed: implemented supported complex unary ops and replaced remaining unary complex stubs with permanent descriptive errors; rch cargo test -p fj-lax passed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
