 {"id":"frankenjax-zrp","title":"Add NaN/Inf gradient propagation tests for AD edge cases","description":"CONTEXT: The AD engine (fj-ad) has no tests verifying how NaN and Inf propagate through VJP/JVP rules. JAX propagates NaN faithfully: grad(sin)(NaN) = NaN, grad(exp)(Inf) = Inf. Silent NaN-to-zero or Inf-to-zero conversion in gradient rules would be a correctness bug that goes undetected.\n\nSCOPE: Add targeted tests in crates/fj-ad/src/lib.rs verifying:\n  1. NaN propagation: grad(sin)(NaN)=NaN, grad(cos)(NaN)=NaN, grad(exp)(NaN)=NaN, grad(log)(NaN)=NaN, grad(tanh)(NaN)=NaN, grad(x^2)(NaN)=NaN\n  2. Inf propagation: grad(exp)(Inf)=Inf, grad(log)(0+)=Inf or -Inf, grad(x^2)(Inf)=Inf, grad(1/x)(0)=(-Inf or NaN)\n  3. Mixed: grad(x*y) where x=NaN, y=finite\n  4. Backward pass with NaN cotangent: vjp(sin, 1.0, NaN) should produce NaN gradient\n  5. JVP with NaN tangent: jvp(sin, 1.0, NaN) should produce NaN output tangent\n\nTESTING: Each test checks is_nan() or is_infinite() on the gradient output. Use descriptive assertion messages. Log each test case.\n\nACCEPTANCE: All NaN/Inf propagation tests pass. No gradient rule silently converts NaN to 0 or Inf to finite.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-04T01:12:34.991960599Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-27T08:56:40.638142102Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T08:56:40.635989505Z","close_reason":"Already covered by AD NaN/Inf propagation tests; verified in full workspace test run","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
